Description: Parent identifier from which the biospecimen was obtained. Parent identifier could be another imCORE biospecimen identifier or an imCORE subject identifier.
List of imCORE biospecimen identifiers (separated by commas) of other biospecimens also derived from this same biospecimen; enter "Not Applicable" if not applicable.
List of imCORE biospecimen identifiers (separated by commas) of experimentally grouped biospecimens; enter "Not Applicable" if not applicable.
Description of experimental grouping design for paired suamples (i.e. tumor/normal). Enter "Not Applicable" if not applicable.
Text term that designates species type. For cell lines or cultured cells, please indiciate the species of origin.
Valid Values: Human, Mouse

Description: Text term that represents a description of the kind of tissue collected with respect to disease status or proximity to tumor tissue. Be as specific as possible; i.e. pre-cancerous lesions should be classified as "Abnormal", and cancerouse as "Tumor."
Valid Values: Abnormal, Normal, Peritumoral, Tumor, Unknown, Not Applicable

Description: Tumor tissue type
Text that describes the kind of disease present in the tumor specimen as related to a specific time point. If tissue_type is "Normal", please enter "Not Applicable" here.
Valid Values: Metastatic, Premalignant, Primary, Recurrence, Xenograft, Unknown, Not Reported, Not Applicable

Description: Text term that represents the kind of molecular specimen analyte.
Valid Values: Cell suspension, DNA, circulating tumor DNA, complementary DNA, RNA, Protein, Not Specified, Not Applicable

Description: Age of the subject at the time of biospecimen collection, expressed in number of days since birth (integer).
Time of day at the time of biospecimen collection, expressed in 24-hour notation format (hh:mm)
Label that best describes the timepoint at which the biospecimen was obtained.
Valid Values: Baseline, Neoadjuvant, Resection, Pre-treatment, On-treatment, End or post treatment, Disease progression, Not Recorded, Not Applicable

Description: Protocols.io identifer that describes the protocol by which the sample was obtained or generated. A valid Digital Object Identifier (DOI) (this would include protocols for collection as well as processing depending on the same. i.e. dissociation)
For tumors in paired organs, designates the side on which the specimen was obtained.
Valid Values: Bilateral, Left, Right, Unknown, Not Reported, Not Applicable

Description: Text term that represents the method used to preserve the sample.
Valid Values: Fresh, Fixed, Frozen, OCT, Unknown, Not Reported, Not Applicable
